<FIRST>u i BC-USEmbassy-Killing     01-28 0145</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-US Embassy-Killing,0147</SECOND>
<HEAD>Wife Of Embassy Official Beaten To Death, Daughter Scalded</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The wife of a U.S. Embassy official was
beaten to death and her nine-month-old daughter scalded with boiling
water by an unknown assailant, embassy spokesman Ross Petzing said
today.
   Petzing said the husband found his 35-year-old wife and stricken
child at their apartment when he returned from work Friday. The
wife, the spokesman said, suffered brutal head injuries.
   Thai police said they were investigating but would provide no
details, saying they were told by the U.S. Embassy not to talk to
the press about the case.
   Petzing refused to identify the wife or husband, except to say
she had been born in Thailand. He did not know whether she was an
American or Thai citizen.
   The child was being treated in a hospital for second-degree
burns, he said.
</TEXT>
