<FIRST>r i PM-Japan-Volcano     01-28 0115</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Japan-Volcano,0119</SECOND>
<HEAD>Volcano Erupts, Minor Earthquakes Detected</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A volcano in northern Japanese island of Hokkaido
erupted three times today, but no damage was reported, officials
said.
   Minor earthquakes accompanied the disturbances on Mount Tokachi,
which has erupted at least 12 times since Dec. 16, an official at
the Asahikawa Meteorological Agency said.
   Volcanic tremors were also detected throughout the day, but no
evacuation orders were issued, said the official, speaking on
condition of anonymity.
   ``Today's eruption appears to be spontaneous and we cannot tell
whether eruptions of similar magnitude will continue or a major
eruption will strike,'' said Hiromu Okada, the head of the Usu
Volcanic Research Laboratory of Hokkaido University.
</TEXT>
