<FIRST>r a PM-Baghead     01-28 0206</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Baghead,0212</SECOND>
<HEAD>Who Turned Out the Lights?</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DERIDDER, La. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   It was a simple oversight that ended the
career of habitual robber J. Douglas Creswell, a Louisiana
prosecutor says.
   Creswell, 51, forgot to cut eyeholes in the plastic garbage bag
he wore in a botched motel holdup last year, according to Keith
Milam, assistant district attorney for Beauregard Parish.
   State District Judge Homer L. Colthorp gave Creswell concurrent
25-year prison sentences Friday for two clothing store holdups a
week before the botched robbery at the Park Motel, Milam said.
   Creswell, armed with a knife, walked into the motel last May and
began pulling a garbage bag over his head, according to a statement
by motel clerk Monica Stroud.
   Creswell suddenly realized he had forgotten to make eyeholes in
the bag, the clerk told police.
   ``So he started pulling on the bag to try to put some holes in
it,'' Milam said. ``And then he asked for the money. Well, she said
she wasn't going to give him any money and he left.''
   The clerk called police and Creswell admitted to the botched
holdup when he was arrested minutes later, Milam said. Authorities
said Creswell previously had been convicted of four armed robberies
in Texas.
</TEXT>
