<SECOND>PM-Polisario,0182</SECOND>
<HEAD>Polisario Front Calls 1-Month Unilateral Truce In Western Sahara</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ALGIERS, Algeria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Polisario Front, which has been
fighting Morocco for independence of the phosphate-rich Western
Sahara for 13 years, announced today a unilateral truce on all
fronts throughout February.
   The announcement, made by the information ministry of the
``Saharan Arab Democratic Republic,'' the Polisario's
government-in-exile, is the group's contribution to improving
conditions for the summit of North African leaders next month in
Marrakech, Morocco, the statement said.
   The statement comes before further expected meetings between
Morocco's King Hassan II and the Marxist group's leaders. Two
meetings between Moroccan representatives and the guerrilla group
were held earlier this month in Marrakech.
   The Polisario statement said the organization had decided on ``a
unilaterial military truce during all of the month of February and
on all fronts of combat.''
   It said the Polisario's participation in the summit of the
Maghreb countries would be defined ``during the next meeting between
His Majesty Hassan II and the (group's) leaders.'' It did not
specify a date for the talks.
</TEXT>
