<FIRST>r a AM-BRF--HotArt     01-28 0141</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Hot Art,0145</SECOND>
<HEAD>Painter Proves Popular with Thieves</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROCKFORD, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Now that he lives in Minneapolis, artist
John Berry has found that his works are becoming hot in his old town.
   Especially hot are three Berry paintings which used to hang in
the Old Rock River Cafe and Deli. Cafe co-owner Mike Leifheit says
he'd like to know where they're hanging now.
   ``He's become our most-stolen artist,'' Leifheit said recently of
Berry.
   The most recent theft occurred early this week, when a painting
depicting Bacchus, the Roman god of wine, was stolen from the deli's
front bar.
   It was the third work by Berry stolen from the cafe, where works
by two other artists also have been taken.
   Berry took news of the latest heist in stride. He noted wryly
that the thief has ``excellent taste'' in art.
</TEXT>
