<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Norway-Weather     01-28 0128</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Norway-Weather,0131</SECOND>
<HEAD>Oslo Has Driest January In 90 Years</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OSLO, Norway (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The capital recorded its driest January on
record, and some city workers spent the month playing cards beside
idle snowplows.
   ``We never had such a warm, dry and snowless January in Oslo and
the surrounding Nordmarka forest area since 1897 when weather began
to be recorded here,'' said spokesman Gustav Bjoerbaek of Oslo's
Meteorological Institute.
   Oslo has had only 0.47 inches of precipitation during the month,
when the normal average is 1.93 inches. Last year it was 5.47
inches. Temperatures which normally hover in the lower 20s have been
in the mid-30s.
   The odd weather has increased poker-playing among city employees,
but it also forced the cancellation of some ski competitions in
eastern Norway.
</TEXT>
