and two counts of endangering the welfare of a minor.
   The son, whose name was not released because he is a juvenile,
was charged with first-degree rape, sodomy and incest.
   Peyton said the daughter was placed in the state's protective
custody program.
   All three were arraigned Saturday and were being held in lieu of
$5,000 bail each, he said.
